    </div>
    
    <div class="faq-grid">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What is a domain name?</h3>
        <p>A domain name is your website's address on the internet. It's what people type in their browser to visit your website (e.g., yourbusiness.com).</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>How long does domain registration take?</h3>
        <p>Domain registration is instant! Once payment is confirmed, your domain is activated immediately and ready to use.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I transfer my existing domain?</h3>
        <p>Yes! You can easily transfer your domain to QuantumBayCloud. The process takes 5-7 days and includes a free 1-year extension.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Do I need hosting to register a domain?</h3>
        <p>No, you can register a domain without hosting. However, you'll need hosting to make your website accessible online.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>What happens when my domain expires?</h3>
        <p>You'll receive renewal reminders before expiration. After expiration, there's a 30-day grace period, followed by a redemption period where recovery fees apply.</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="faq-item">
        <h3>Can I get a refund on domain registration?</h3>
        <p>Domain registrations are non-refundable as they are registered with third-party registries. However, you can cancel auto-renewal anytime.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

